## 4. Fix the `JitHelp_commit()` high-PC rejection

This code is unsafe:

```cpp
if (pc >= 0x80000000u) {
    g_exitReason[cpu] = EXIT_FALLBACK;
    return -1;
}
```

ARM9 BIOS lives at `0xFFFF0000`, which is a valid guest PC in NDS mode. Rejecting every address above `0x80000000` is wrong.

Replace it with:

```cpp
int JitHelp_commit(Interpreter* interp, int cpu,
                   uint32_t* regs, uint32_t cpsr,
                   uint32_t pc, int reason) {
    if (!interp || !regs || cpu < 0 || cpu > 1)
        return -1;

    uint32_t** p = interp->getRegisters();
    if (!p)
        return -1;

    for (int i = 0; i < 15; i++) {
        if (!p[i])
            return -1;

        *p[i] = regs[i];
    }

    interp->getCpsrRef() = cpsr;

    g_exitPC[cpu]     = pc;
    g_exitCPSR[cpu]   = cpsr;
    g_exitReason[cpu] = reason;

    if (reason == EXIT_NORMAL)
        interp->setPC(pc);

    return 0;
}
```

Your existing `validPC()` checks already decide whether the JIT can compile/execute a PC. `JitHelp_commit()` should only commit machine state.

