## 7. Keep these PowerPC branches unchanged

These are correct and should remain exactly as they are:

```cpp
ctx.E(ppc_bc(12, 2, 8)); // beq
```

and:

```cpp
ctx.base[idx] = ppc_bc(12, 2, (int16_t)off); // beq
```

Your PPC branch helper is fine:

```cpp
static inline uint32_t ppc_bc(uint8_t bo, uint8_t bi, int16_t off, bool lk = false) {
    return (16u << 26) | ((bo & 31u) << 21) | ((bi & 31u) << 16) |
           ((uint32_t)(off & 0xFFFC)) | (lk ? 1u : 0u);
}
```

For your use case:

```cpp
ppc_bc(12, 2, offset)
```

means effectively:

```asm
beq cr0, target
```

which is what your code intends.

